        "kind": "pull_request",
        "title": "feat(reply): persist session preferences",
        "body": "## Summary\n\nThis PR adds explicit `--persist` support for reply preferences that users may want to survive session rollover:\n\n- `/usage <mode> --persist`\n- `/thinking <level> --persist` / `/think <level> --persist`\n- `/model <provider/model> --persist`\n\nPersistent intent is tracked with `persistentPreferenceFields`, so rollover can distinguish durable user preferences from ordinary session-local overrides.\n\n## Why\n\nSome reply preferences currently behave like transcript-local session state. When a session rolls over after a daily or idle boundary, settings such as `/usage full` disappear even when users intended them as durable preferences.\n\nThe explicit flag keeps existing behavior safe by default: preferences remain temporary unless the user opts in with `--persist`.\n\n## Behavior\n\n- Persisted `/usage` values survive daily and idle session rollover.\n- Non-persisted `/usage` values continue to be dropped on rollover.\n- `/model` and `/thinking` acknowledge and record the same persistence intent consistently with `/usage`.\n- `--persist` is stripped from agent-visible directive text.\n- Ordinary user messages containing `--persist` are not rewritten.\n- A later non-`--persist` update clears the stale marker for that field, so `/usage tokens` after `/usage full --persist` becomes temporary again instead of accidentally surviving the next rollover.\n\n## Evidence\n\nReal behavior covered by focused tests:\n\n- `/usage full --persist` writes `responseUsage: \"full\"` plus `persistentPreferenceFields: [\"responseUsage\"]`.\n- Daily rollover preserves persisted `responseUsage`.\n- Daily rollover drops non-persisted `responseUsage`, preserving the existing default behavior.\n- `/think high --persist` and `/model openai/gpt-4o --persist` store persistent markers and strip `--persist` from agent-visible text.\n- Non-persistent follow-up updates clear stale markers for `/usage`, `/think`, and `/model`, including mixed-content directive paths.\n- Ordinary messages containing `--persist` remain unchanged.\n\nLatest validation on current head `4edfd5b13a8ecb317546e786faa0a21d7e2e0666`:\n\n```bash\nnode scripts/run-vitest.mjs run src/auto-reply/reply/commands-session-usage.test.ts src/auto-reply/reply/directive-handling.model.test.ts src/auto-reply/reply/session.test.ts\n```\n\nResult: 3 test files passed, 207 tests passed.\n\n```bash\nnode scripts/run-tsgo.mjs -p test/tsconfig/tsconfig.core.test.json --incremental --tsBuildInfoFile .artifacts/tsgo-cache/core-test.tsbuildinfo\nnode_modules/.bin/oxfmt --check src/auto-reply/reply/commands-session.ts src/auto-reply/reply/directive-handling.impl.ts src/auto-reply/reply/directive-handling.persist.ts src/auto-reply/reply/commands-session-usage.test.ts src/auto-reply/reply/directive-handling.model.test.ts\ngit diff --check\n```\n\nResult: all passed.\n\nAdditional validation previously run on this branch:\n\n```bash\nnode scripts/run-vitest.mjs run src/auto-reply/reply.directive.parse.test.ts src/auto-reply/reply/commands-session-usage.test.ts src/auto-reply/reply/directive-handling.model.test.ts src/auto-reply/reply/session.test.ts\nnode scripts/run-tsgo.mjs -p test/tsconfig/tsconfig.extensions.test.json --incremental --tsBuildInfoFile .artifacts/tsgo-cache/extensions-test.tsbuildinfo\n```\n\nResult: 4 related test files passed, 240 tests passed, and extensions typecheck passed.\n\n## Related Issues\n\nRelated: #17102, #12578\n",
